reviewText: These 4 films are a bargain when bought as a combo. All are worth watching and are made pretty well. Pure Country has great music and a good feel good story about mistakes and human nature and Macon County line is just a good realistic movie and well made. Mistaken identiy and devastating results. Honey Suckle Rose is good even though I am not a Willie Nelson fan. He was pretty good in Barbaros but Gary Busey was better in Barbarosa.I enjoy movies that keep me watching wondering how they will end and these 3 did that. I would rate the entire package as a 5 and each separate movie as pretty close to a 4 star. A lucky buy and a bargain.

reviewText: This is a great set of movies. "Honeysuckle Rose", "Pure Country", The Ballad of Little Jo" and "Macon County Line" make up the set. I'm so happy to have found this set because one of the movies couldn't be found on it's own. I would recommend the set to anyone that loves western movies.
